  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Lexer
    public interface Lexer The lexer will take the raw LISP code and turn it into a queue of tokens to be read by the parser.
    Parser
    public interface Parser The parser will take a token queue and turn it into an abstract syntax tree (AST) to be passed to the eval machine
